    "what_description": "Cyperus welwitschii is a perennial sedge that belongs to the family Cyperaceae. It is characterized by its slender, glabrous stems, which grow up to 1.5 meters tall, and its linear-lanceolate leaves that are 5-30 cm long and 1-4 mm wide. The inflorescence is a terminal spike, 5-20 cm long, composed of 3-10 spikelets, each bearing 2-8 glumes and 2-4 fertile florets. The plant produces brownish-yellow flowers, 2-3 mm long, which are wind-pollinated. The fruit is a dark brown nut, 2-3 mm long, with a prominent beak.",
